None of these countries has an army,
or for that matter, weapons.

1151
01:16:33,323 --> 01:16:37,326
So it looked like we'd be doing
most of the invading stuff ourselves.

1152
01:16:38,487 --> 01:16:42,090
- Then there was also:
- Romania.

1153
01:16:42,250 --> 01:16:46,934
The Kingdom of Morocco.

1154
01:16:47,094 --> 01:16:50,097
Morocco wasn't officially
a member of the coalition...

1155
01:16:50,257 --> 01:16:53,460
...but according to one report, they did
offer to send 2000 monkeys...

1156
01:16:53,620 --> 01:16:55,622
...to help detonate land mines.

1157
01:16:57,223 --> 01:16:58,945
These are men of vision.

1158
01:16:58,985 --> 01:17:00,706
The Netherlands.

1159
01:17:00,786 --> 01:17:02,588
And I'm proud to call them allies.

1160
01:17:04,149 --> 01:17:06,151
Afghanistan.

1161
01:17:06,271 --> 01:17:08,152
Afghanistan?

1162
01:17:08,232 --> 01:17:10,514
Oh, yeah. They had an army.

1163
01:17:10,675 --> 01:17:14,678
Our army. I guess that's one way
to build a coalition.

1164
01:17:14,838 --> 01:17:17,240
Just keep invading countries.

1165
01:17:17,440 --> 01:17:21,644
Yes, with our mighty coalition intact,
we were ready.

1166
01:17:21,804 --> 01:17:25,407
One could almost say
it's the mother of all coalitions.

1167
01:17:28,049 --> 01:17:31,052
Fortunately, we have an independent
media in this country...

1168
01:17:31,212 --> 01:17:33,214
...who would tell us the truth.

1169
01:17:33,294 --> 01:17:37,377
The rallying around the president,
the flag and the troops has begun.

1170
01:17:37,498 --> 01:17:39,099
And we're gonna win!

1171
01:17:39,139 --> 01:17:41,741
You have to be with troops
to understand the adrenaline.

1172
01:17:41,941 --> 01:17:44,464
I want you to know,
I think Navy SEALs rock.

1173
01:17:44,504 --> 01:17:47,626
The pictures you're seeing
are absolutely phenomenal.

1174
01:17:47,746 --> 01:17:52,270
When my country's at war,
I want my country to win.

1175
01:17:52,390 --> 01:17:55,873
Iraqi opposition has faded
in the face of American power.

1176
01:17:56,033 --> 01:18:00,437
What you're watching here is truly
historic television and journalism.

1177
01:18:00,597 --> 01:18:01,999
It was absolutely electrifying.

1178
01:18:02,199 --> 01:18:05,602
They had to strap me in with my
camera at the back of the plane.

1179
01:18:05,682 --> 01:18:08,084
An awesome, synchronized
killing machine.

1180
01:18:08,244 --> 01:18:09,725
There is an inherent bias...

1181
01:18:09,925 --> 01:18:12,648
...in the coverage of the American
press in general.

1182
01:18:12,728 --> 01:18:15,130
Am I slanted and biased?
You damn well bet I am.

1183
01:18:19,374 --> 01:18:21,976
But one story the media
wasn't covering...

1184
01:18:22,176 --> 01:18:23,857
...was the personal story...

1185
01:18:24,018 --> 01:18:27,420
...of each and every soldier
who was killed in the war.

1186
01:18:27,581 --> 01:18:30,063
The government would not allow
any cameras...

1187
01:18:30,223 --> 01:18:32,425
...to show the coffins coming home.

1188
01:18:33,145 --> 01:18:35,828
That kind of story is a downer...

1189
01:18:35,908 --> 01:18:39,791
...especially when you're getting
ready for a party on a boat.

1190
01:19:21,987 --> 01:19:23,188
My fellow Americans...

1191
01:19:24,750 --> 01:19:28,153
...major combat operations
in Iraq have ended.

1192
01:19:28,353 --> 01:19:30,154
In the battle of Iraq...

1193
01:19:30,314 --> 01:19:35,119
...the United States
and our allies have prevailed.

1194
01:19:45,928 --> 01:19:47,930
Get out of the way!

1195
01:19:55,176 --> 01:19:58,459
Move! Move! Move! Move!

1196
01:20:18,195 --> 01:20:21,198
162, the number of troops
killed by hostile fire.

1197
01:20:21,398 --> 01:20:25,081
- 244 U.S. Troops...
- 384 U.S. Troops lost their lives...

1198
01:20:25,161 --> 01:20:28,164
- Total killed, 484.
- Died in the line of duty, 500...

1199
01:20:28,244 --> 01:20:29,565
631 American troops...

1200
01:20:29,725 --> 01:20:32,007
More than 825 troops
have been killed in Iraq.

1201
01:20:32,208 --> 01:20:35,010
The largest number of American
military deaths since Vietnam.

1202
01:20:35,170 --> 01:20:41,175
There are some who feel like
that if they attack us...

1203
01:20:41,335 --> 01:20:43,938
...that we may decide
to leave prematurely.

1204
01:20:44,698 --> 01:20:47,100
They don't understand,
if that's the case.

1205
01:20:47,300 --> 01:20:49,102
Let me finish.

1206
01:20:49,983 --> 01:20:54,186
There are some who feel like
the conditions are such...

1207
01:20:54,347 --> 01:20:56,148
...that they can attack us there.

1208
01:20:56,348 --> 01:20:58,030
My answer is, bring them on.

1209
01:21:11,962 --> 01:21:14,764
The United States was planning
on walking through here...

1210
01:21:14,924 --> 01:21:17,246
...like it was gonna be easy and all.

1211
01:21:17,446 --> 01:21:20,649
But it's not that easy
to conquer a country, is it?

1212
01:21:27,135 --> 01:21:31,138
The renewed battle for control
of Iraq raged for a fourth day today...

1213
01:21:31,298 --> 01:21:34,581
...with street clashes in nearly
every corner of the country.

1214
01:21:34,741 --> 01:21:37,343
Iraq could become "another Vietnam. "

1215
01:21:37,584 --> 01:21:40,987
Officials say they see evidence
that Sunni and Shiite extremists...

1216
01:21:41,147 --> 01:21:42,668
...might be joining forces.

1217
01:21:42,748 --> 01:21:44,870
They're not happy they're occupied.

1218
01:21:45,831 --> 01:21:48,433
I wouldn't be happy
if I were occupied either.

1219
01:21:57,961 --> 01:22:00,243
Two Japanese aid workers
and a journalist...

1220
01:22:00,403 --> 01:22:02,405
...kidnapped by men calling
themselves...

1221
01:22:02,605 --> 01:22:04,527
...the Mujahideen Squadrons.

1222
01:22:04,567 --> 01:22:06,769
They threatened to burn
the hostages alive...

1223
01:22:06,969 --> 01:22:11,172
...if Japan does not withdraw its troops
from Iraq within three days.

1224
01:22:11,733 --> 01:22:13,334
What's happened?

1225
01:22:15,656 --> 01:22:16,937
They attacked our convoy.

1226
01:22:17,938 --> 01:22:19,259
You wanna give us your name?

1227
01:22:19,820 --> 01:22:22,422
Hamill, Thomas.

1228
01:22:23,423 --> 01:22:26,626
The Pentagon might keep up
to 24,000 troops in combat...

1229
01:22:26,786 --> 01:22:28,067
...beyond their tour.

1230
01:22:28,267 --> 01:22:30,589
I know our numbers
in the military have gone down.

1231
01:22:30,749 --> 01:22:32,431
They talk about retention.

1232
01:22:33,992 --> 01:22:36,194
I never expected
to be deployed this long.

1233
01:22:36,394 --> 01:22:37,715
I don't think anybody did.

1234
01:22:37,955 --> 01:22:40,878
I don't have any clue
as to why we're still in Iraq.

1235
01:22:40,918 --> 01:22:44,321
If Donald Rumsfeld was here,
I'd ask him for his resignation.

1236
01:22:45,602 --> 01:22:47,604
With the war not going
as planned...

1237
01:22:48,084 --> 01:22:50,887
...and the military in need
of many more troops...

1238
01:22:51,647 --> 01:22:54,169
...where would they find
the new recruits?

1239
01:22:54,370 --> 01:22:56,371
Military experts say three times...

1240
01:22:56,571 --> 01:22:58,773
...the 120,000 U.S. Troops
now deployed...

1241
01:22:58,973 --> 01:23:02,857
...would be needed to pacify
and rebuild the country.

1242
01:23:03,938 --> 01:23:06,820
They would find them
all across America...

1243
01:23:06,900 --> 01:23:10,583
...in the places that had been
destroyed by the economy.

1244
01:23:11,064 --> 01:23:13,666
Places where one
of the only jobs available...

1245
01:23:13,866 --> 01:23:15,748
...was to join the Army.

1246
01:23:15,908 --> 01:23:19,031
Places like my hometown
of Flint, Michigan.

1247
01:23:19,071 --> 01:23:20,792
I was watching TV one day...

1248
01:23:20,872 --> 01:23:24,876
...and they showed some of the areas
that had been hit by bombs.

1249
01:23:24,956 --> 01:23:27,038
And while watching,
I got to thinking...

1250
01:23:27,238 --> 01:23:29,440
...there's parts of Flint
that look like that.

1251
01:23:29,600 --> 01:23:31,121
And we ain't been in a war.

1252
01:23:31,762 --> 01:23:33,643
Look at the neighborhood I live in.

1253
01:23:33,763 --> 01:23:36,165
Most of them are abandoned.
You know, I mean...

1254
01:23:36,326 --> 01:23:38,928
...that's not right.
You wanna talk about terrorism?

1255
01:23:39,128 --> 01:23:42,411
Come right here. President Bush,
right here. Come right here.

1256
01:23:42,571 --> 01:23:44,973
He knows about this corner.
I e-mailed him.

1257
01:23:45,734 --> 01:23:48,256
At the end of January of '04...

1258
01:23:48,336 --> 01:23:51,138
...the unemployment rate
in Flint was 17 percent.

1259
01:23:51,258 --> 01:23:53,861
But you have to take
into consideration as well...

1260
01:23:53,981 --> 01:23:56,983
...that when your unemployment
runs out you're no longer counted.

1261
01:23:57,143 --> 01:24:00,226
I would say that we're close
to at least 50 percent...

1262
01:24:00,386 --> 01:24:03,189
...not working or underemployed.

1263
01:24:03,389 --> 01:24:06,311
Because being underemployed
is just as dangerous.

1264
01:24:06,872 --> 01:24:09,154
My family has gone through
the welfare system...

1265
01:24:09,354 --> 01:24:10,675
...when it was Job Central.

1266
01:24:10,755 --> 01:24:13,958
In the mid-'80s I came through
the job training partnership program.

1267
01:24:16,520 --> 01:24:18,322
I went to a secretary school.

1268
01:24:18,522 --> 01:24:22,125
Years later, I'm executive assistant
to the president of the agency.

1269
01:24:22,285 --> 01:24:23,886
Interesting.

1270
01:24:24,006 --> 01:24:25,888
My mother used to tell me
all the time:

1271
01:24:26,048 --> 01:24:28,170
"Why do you always go
for the underdog?"

1272
01:24:28,370 --> 01:24:30,572
It was because the underdog
is who needed me.

1273
01:24:30,732 --> 01:24:34,215
People that don't have anything,
that's who I have to fight for.

1274
01:24:34,375 --> 01:24:36,577
And that's who I have fought for
my entire life.

1275
01:24:36,777 --> 01:24:39,700
I started taking my children
and telling my children:

1276
01:24:39,740 --> 01:24:41,261
"The military is a good option.

1277
01:24:41,461 --> 01:24:44,464
I can't afford to have you
go to college. I can't pay your way.

1278
01:24:44,504 --> 01:24:46,105
Financial aid will not help you. "

1279
01:24:46,306 --> 01:24:48,708
So I, as a mother,
started teaching my children...

1280
01:24:48,948 --> 01:24:51,150
...about the options
that the military could do.

1281
01:24:51,310 --> 01:24:53,031
They would take them
around the world.

1282
01:24:53,232 --> 01:24:56,434
They'd see all the things that I,
as a mother, couldn't let them see.

1283
01:24:56,594 --> 01:25:00,478
It'd pay for their education that I, as
their mother and father, couldn't pay.

1284
01:25:00,638 --> 01:25:03,160
The military is a good option
for kids in Flint.

1285
01:25:03,320 --> 01:25:06,323
The military is an excellent option
for the people of Flint.

1286
01:25:07,884 --> 01:25:11,487
How many of you have a friend
or a family member in the service?

1287
01:25:13,049 --> 01:25:15,531
Anybody currently serving
overseas?

1288
01:25:15,691 --> 01:25:17,492
- A brother of mine.
- My cousin.

1289
01:25:17,693 --> 01:25:18,894
Yeah, cousin.

1290
01:25:19,094 --> 01:25:21,015
- Where's your brother?
- Iraq.

1291
01:25:21,055 --> 01:25:22,977
Germany.

1292
01:25:23,057 --> 01:25:27,181
My cousin got shipped off
to Iraq, like, three days ago.

1293
01:25:27,381 --> 01:25:28,782
Dang.

1294
01:25:28,982 --> 01:25:31,184
There's, like, an Army
or Navy recruiter...

1295
01:25:31,344 --> 01:25:34,747
...or Marines recruiter up there
almost every week...

1296
01:25:35,388 --> 01:25:39,391
...in the lunchroom recruiting
students at the lunchroom.

1297
01:25:39,952 --> 01:25:43,355
There are people with a calling.

1298
01:25:46,517 --> 01:25:50,841
Most serve one weekend a month
and two weeks a year.

1299
01:25:52,883 --> 01:25:54,604
Earning money for college.

1300
01:25:58,367 --> 01:26:00,769
Protecting their community.

1301
01:26:02,131 --> 01:26:04,413
In the Army National Guard...

1302
01:26:04,933 --> 01:26:06,214
...you can.

1303
01:26:09,217 --> 01:26:10,538
I'm going into the Air Force.

1304
01:26:10,698 --> 01:26:13,701
I'm gonna take a year off
after high school.

1305
01:26:13,861 --> 01:26:17,264
And then make a career. I wanna be
an aircraft maintenance technician.

1306
01:26:17,424 --> 01:26:20,426
I ran into a recruiter, and there
was something I noticed about it.

1307
01:26:20,586 --> 01:26:23,269
And this is kind of on another...
I noticed it was odd.

1308
01:26:23,469 --> 01:26:26,191
More like he was hiring me
than recruiting me for the Army.

1309
01:26:26,351 --> 01:26:29,434
It was the way he approached me.
I was in Borders Books and Music.

1310
01:26:29,634 --> 01:26:31,836
He came up like he was handing
us a business card.

1311
01:26:31,996 --> 01:26:34,518
He had business cards
made for the Army.

1312
01:26:39,843 --> 01:26:42,325
Meet Marine Staff
Sergeant Dale Kortman...

1313
01:26:42,565 --> 01:26:44,567
...and Sergeant Raymond Plouhar.

1314
01:26:45,728 --> 01:26:49,732
They are two of the many recruiters
assigned to Flint, Michigan.

1315
01:26:50,092 --> 01:26:52,094
They're very busy these days.

1316
01:26:52,294 --> 01:26:54,295
Look, he's running away already.

1317
01:26:54,496 --> 01:26:57,098
- He's seen us coming.
- Yeah.

1318
01:26:57,979 --> 01:26:59,580
What have we got here?

1319
01:26:59,660 --> 01:27:01,982
- Need a little gangster.
- Yeah.

1320
01:27:02,422 --> 01:27:05,145
We're heading over
to the Courtland Mall right now.

1321
01:27:06,186 --> 01:27:08,107
They decided not to go
to the wealthier...

1322
01:27:08,307 --> 01:27:10,589
...Genesee Valley Mall
in the suburbs.

1323
01:27:10,750 --> 01:27:13,672
They have a hard time
recruiting young people there.

1324
01:27:13,752 --> 01:27:17,155
Instead, they went
to the other mall.

1325
01:27:17,235 --> 01:27:19,917
- Let's go in through Mervyn's.
- In through Mervyn's.

1326
01:27:20,118 --> 01:27:23,921
And then we'll walk straight down
and straight back and then go down...

1327
01:27:24,321 --> 01:27:26,323
Gents, you know
we're looking at you, right?

1328
01:27:26,443 --> 01:27:28,164
You guys ever think
about joining up?

1329
01:27:28,245 --> 01:27:30,847
I thought about going to college
and playing basketball.

1330
01:27:31,007 --> 01:27:33,409
- You any good?
- Yeah. Especially basketball.

1331
01:27:33,609 --> 01:27:35,731
Good. You can play ball
for the Marine Corps.

1332
01:27:35,891 --> 01:27:38,694
Travel around the world
for the Corps basketball team.

1333
01:27:38,894 --> 01:27:41,296
- David Robinson was in the military.
- Oh, was he?

1334
01:27:41,456 --> 01:27:43,137
Yeah, you can definitely hook it up.

1335
01:27:43,338 --> 01:27:46,861
Right now somebody out there wants
to be a Marine but has no idea how to.

1336
01:27:47,021 --> 01:27:49,223
- Where you work at?
- I work at KFC.

1337
01:27:49,303 --> 01:27:52,505
- Sweet. Hook us up with deals.
- Yes.

1338
01:27:52,666 --> 01:27:54,387
They're waiting to get recruited.

1339
01:27:54,587 --> 01:27:56,669
I was gonna try a career
in music or something.

1340
01:27:56,829 --> 01:28:00,152
Career in music? Maybe we can
get you a career in music.

1341
01:28:00,352 --> 01:28:03,155
Let the Marines go for it.
I'm sure you know who Shaggy is.

1342
01:28:03,635 --> 01:28:07,558
- You know anything about him?
- Yeah, he's the Jamaican singer.

1343
01:28:07,598 --> 01:28:09,720
How about a former Marine?

1344
01:28:09,800 --> 01:28:11,402
- Oh.
- Did you know it?

1345
01:28:11,562 --> 01:28:14,284
You need to know discipline
if you're gonna get into music.

1346
01:28:14,364 --> 01:28:16,166
Especially discipline
with the money.

1347
01:28:16,326 --> 01:28:18,728
If you make a million, you need
to manage that money.

1348
01:28:18,848 --> 01:28:20,449
Come to the office, we can talk...

1349
01:28:20,609 --> 01:28:22,491
...show you everything
about the Marines.

1350
01:28:22,691 --> 01:28:25,013
- A plan?
- What you got going this afternoon?

1351
01:28:25,173 --> 01:28:27,856
How about tomorrow?
10:00 Monday morning?

1352
01:28:28,056 --> 01:28:30,978
- That sounds pretty good.
- You want me to pick you up?

1353
01:28:31,139 --> 01:28:33,621
It's better to get them
when they're in ones and twos...

1354
01:28:33,821 --> 01:28:35,542
...and work on them that way.

1355
01:28:35,742 --> 01:28:36,944
Ladies, ready to join up?

1356
01:28:37,104 --> 01:28:39,105
Green hat right behind us.

1357
01:28:39,306 --> 01:28:42,909
- Looks young. He's young.
- Yeah.

1358
01:28:43,069 --> 01:28:45,271
We got two over here...

1359
01:28:45,431 --> 01:28:47,312
...right over by the red van.

1360
01:28:47,433 --> 01:28:49,634
You go that way, I go this way,
we corner them.

1361
01:28:49,714 --> 01:28:51,716
- You're in the ninth grade?
- Yes, sir.

1362
01:28:51,876 --> 01:28:54,679
Man, you look older
than ninth grade.

1363
01:28:54,879 --> 01:28:56,600
All right, here's my card.

1364
01:28:56,640 --> 01:28:58,642
You ever thought about
being a Marine, man?

1365
01:28:58,842 --> 01:29:01,164
I've thought about it.
I've got a wife and kid now.

1366
01:29:01,324 --> 01:29:02,926
Even more reason to join up.

1367
01:29:03,126 --> 01:29:04,727
What I want to do, man...

1368
01:29:04,928 --> 01:29:08,010
...is get information from you
so I can scratch you off my list...

1369
01:29:08,090 --> 01:29:11,773
...saying I've talked to you, and
you're not interested. Is that cool?

1370
01:29:11,853 --> 01:29:14,256
What's your name? Phone number?
What's your address?

1371
01:29:14,496 --> 01:29:15,897
Add another one to the list.

1372
01:29:16,057 --> 01:29:20,661
However, one would love to have
that chance to experience college life.

1373
01:29:20,701 --> 01:29:23,904
You know, stuff young people
can do without having the risk...

1374
01:29:24,024 --> 01:29:27,307
...of dying in the process,
I guess I can say candidly.

1375
01:29:29,589 --> 01:29:33,872
The holidays add a bit more friction,
as opposed to just another night...

1376
01:29:34,033 --> 01:29:38,236
...in the fact we wanna give our guys
a little time off, time to relax.

1377
01:29:38,316 --> 01:29:42,320
However, we are in a combat zone,
and my soldiers do recognize that fact.

1378
01:29:42,480 --> 01:29:45,562
Everybody's a little bit
nervous about it, I guess.

1379
01:29:45,642 --> 01:29:48,645
We're professionals.
We're gonna take care of you.

1380
01:29:49,686 --> 01:29:51,608
I promise.

1381
01:29:52,689 --> 01:29:56,612
Every house here has the right
to have weapons.

1382
01:29:56,772 --> 01:29:58,974
Maximum, one AK-47.

